Important Question 🙋‍♀️!!! 

Should you wait a little after doing your skincare before applying makeup?

There’s no strict rule—but giving your skin a few minutes can actually tell you a lot about how healthy and balanced it is.

When we rush into makeup right after skincare, things can go wrong—foundation may not sit well, your skin might feel sticky or dry in patches, or products can start balling up on the surface.

In this reel, I explain why taking that small pause can make your makeup look smoother, last longer, and actually feel better.

Sometimes, all your skin needs is a moment to breathe and settle.

What do YOU do ?? 🤷‍♀️
Have you ever tried waiting between skincare and makeup? 
Or do you usually apply one right after the other?
Let me know in your comments 📝

latestPosts.caption:
Answering one of your questions today…🗒️

Generally, You really don’t need a lot of powder—especially if you’re already using a powder-finish foundation. 
A light touch is enough to set your base without taking away its natural glow. Powder is meant to support, not take over. 
And if your makeup ever starts to look a bit too matte or dry, a hydrating mist can help settle everything beautifully and bring back that soft, lived-in finish.
Have you tried this trick before? Let me know what works for you—or drop your makeup questions below, I’d love to answer them.
